 the Métis nation to make political claims as a people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMétisxEthnic identity. 0aMétisxHistory. 0aMétisxLegal status, laws, etc. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311141999240uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482723240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774827232423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774827232/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-141999-2  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles